                    <h3>What Is Solar Energy?</h3>
                    <p>With the sun's rays constantly beaming down upon earth there could be enough energy to satisfy global energy needs for an entire year or more. Technology can be used to harness the sun's energy and make it useable. Free and an inexhaustible resource, solar energy is a great alternative and harnessing it is a relatively new idea. Using solar power as a heat source was the first discovery in harnessing solar energy. The first solar collector was built in 1767 by a Swiss scientist named Horace de Saussure. The second discovery was that electricity could be produced through solar energy.</p>
